<TITLE> Three BDR men give statements </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 3 (bdnews24.com)  Three BDR members gave 'confessional statements' Friday in Pilkhana BDR mutiny case. Chief metropolitan magistrates Faisal Atique-bin-Quader and Zulfiqar Hayat recorded the statements of Nayek Mohammad Abdul Kaiyum, Habildar Masud Iqbal and Sepoy Manjur Alam from 3pm to 8pm. They were sent to jail later, assistant sub-inspector Asab Ahmed and constable Zillur Rahman at the recording office of the court said. The CID also brought eight BDR members arrested anew before the same CMM's Court. The investigation officer, assistant superintendent of police Abdul Kahar Akand sought 10 days to grill one of the accused, Sepoy Saiful Islam. The court granted him seven days and sent seven other accused to jail. The CID brought 11 more BDR members before the court and sought five days to interrogate eight of them. The court granted three days to grill the eight. The rest three were later sent to jail. On Mar 25, six BDR personnel gave confessional statements in the case for around eight hour
